descriptor.name: OKRA ADVANTA LAVANYA
descriptor.long_desc:
These seeds are small dark brown in colour and round in shape. The fruit is ready in 80-85 days from the sowing of this seed. The fruit weighs an average of 8 to 10 kg. The fruit is dark red in appearance and very sweet in taste. This variety of watermelon is rich in properties and it also has immunity to reduce diseases like Fusarium wilt.

Technical Specifications:
Sowing time: February
Soil: loamy soil rich in organic matter
First crop: 80-85 days after sowing
Seed quantity per acre: 1.5 kg to 1.8 kg per acre
Sowing distance between rows/ridges: 2.5 m. 3 m from
Sowing distance between plants: 60 cm to 60 cm
Sowing Depth:2-2.5cm
 
Speciality:
Colour: Light green with dark green stripes
Shape: Oval
Weight: 8 to 10 kg
 It is a high-quality fruit.
This is a high-quality seed that produces a great yield.
The pod has 9-10 seeds  

Field Preparations: 
- Prepare the field well in advance. After the harvest of the Kharif crop, plough the soil with the initial need for Nitrogen, in the crops add 20 kg Nitrogen with 60 kg Phosphorus.
- Protect against weed such as Bathua, Senji, Krishan Neel, spray a solution made by mixing 4-5 L of Stamp 30 ( Pendimethalin) in 600-800L water immediately after sowing the pea seeds. It will control the weeds quite a bit.

Fertilizers and Pesticides:
- At the time of land preparation, apply 8 to 10 tonnes per acre of manure. In this, use cow dung, compost, 60-80 kg nitrogen, 50 kg phosphorus and 50 kg potash per 1 hectare. 
- Just before planting, spray the herbicide Pendimethalin at the rate of 1 kg/ha.
- To save red worms at the time of germination, sprinkle carbaryl 50 dust at the rate of 20 kg 1 hectare.
- Malathion 50 EC or Endosulfan 35 EC 1000 ml for protection against fruit flies. Took. Spray on a per hectare basis.

descriptor.name: BOTTLEGOURD MAHYCO MAHY 8
descriptor.long_desc:
A prolific bearer fruits are attractive green, tender, cylindrical with 55 -60 cm in length. Each fruit weighs 500 – 550 g. The rind is smooth flesh is white with slow seed maturity makes it an excellent hybrid.
Fruit Shape: Cylindrical fruit
Fruit color: Attractive green
Maturity time: 45-50 days
Very high vigorous
Very high yielding
Tolerant to disease
Growing Conditions: Bottle gourd can be grown in wide range of soils. But it thrives well in sandy loam soils. The land or main field should be prepared thoroughly by six to seven ploughings and pH range in soil should be from 6.5 to 7.5 in bottle gourd cultivation.
Season: Kharif/ Rabi/ Summer
Seed Rate : 500-600 grams / acre (1 acre = 43560 square feet)
Yield: Approximately 15 - 20 Tonne / acre
